Fix confirmed. The issue was `INTERVAL %s` — PostgreSQL can't bind parameters to INTERVAL literals directly. Changed to `%s::interval` which casts the parameterized string `'24 hours'` to an interval type. The query now executes successfully (0 windows cleaned, meaning no stale windows exist).
